##
## Kiro Linux — Arch mirrorlist (curated, robust default)
##
## This is the mirrorlist that ships on the live ISO and is copied to the
## installed system by Calamares. It is intentionally SHORT: a handful of
## geo-routed CDN mirrors that are fast and complete *everywhere on earth*,
## so an install never depends on a long tail of slow or dead mirrors.
##
## Why not a full country list? pacman spreads ParallelDownloads across the
## active Server lines; a 600-entry worldwide list means many downloads hit
## dead/slow hosts and the install crawls or fails. These geo CDNs route each
## user to their nearest healthy datacenter automatically — no tuning needed.
##
## Want the fastest *local* mirrors after install? Run:
##     sudo reflector --latest 20 --sort rate --save /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist
##

## Geo-routed CDN mirrors (each picks the nearest datacenter automatically)
Server = https://geo.mirror.pkgbuild.com/$repo/os/$arch
Server = https://fastly.mirror.pkgbuild.com/$repo/os/$arch

## High-capacity global mirrors (fallbacks)
Server = https://mirrors.kernel.org/archlinux/$repo/os/$arch
Server = https://mirror.rackspace.com/archlinux/$repo/os/$arch
